     "body" => "connects thinkthroughmath/storyboard#2630\r\nconnects thinkthroughmath/storyboard#2635\r\nconnects thinkthroughmath/storyboard#2636\r\n\r\n## Testing notes for testing from farms\r\nSo this isn't great, we know, but this is how you can test rtc with\r\nstudent clients on production.\r\n\r\n- Login as student or preview activity\r\n- Launch LT session\r\n- Open inspector and copy iframe url\r\n- Close existing LP LT session\r\n- Paste into new tab\r\n  - Add `&ffRtc=true` to your query string\r\n  - Press enter\r\n- Add student\r\n- You should now be able to communicate via rtc with the student\r\n\r\nWe did this to avoid this needing to have lockstep PR's with Apangea and\r\nLP in order to test.  The idea is to keep this disabled in Prod for a while for\r\nnormal users.\r\n\r\n## To Test\r\n- [ ] Login as a teacher\r\n- [ ] Login as fake student with rtc enabled (`student-mc-testRtc`)\r\n- [ ] Login as a real student using the iframe trickery mentioned above\r\n- [ ] Connect to both students\r\n- [ ] Notice your audio will always be available on one of the students at any given time\r\n- [ ] Switch between each student, you will likely hear some faint clicking as the audio inputs switch\r\n- [ ] Login as a student without flash (another real or any other fake student)\r\n- [ ] Ensure you hear no audio when on the flash student's screen unless you are pushing the talk button\r\n\r\n### Note: The `Talk` button on RTC chats is superficial and has no actual behavior\r\n",
     "closed_at" => nil,
     "comments" => [%{"body" => "@seejee @TheJefe can you comment on the final commit's testing info to see if this is acceptable as a feature flag to avoid lockstep merges?",
