  "prod-scripts" => [%{"assignee" => nil,
     "body" => "Fixes [storyboard#2733](https://github.com/thinkthroughmath/storyboard/issues/2733)\r\n\r\n**Why Do I Exist?**\r\nThis script was written to be run after [apangea#3079](https://github.com/thinkthroughmath/apangea/pull/3079) gets deployed to production. It was written to cleanup any extraneous entities that should not be active under an inactive Customer.\r\n\r\n**How Do I Test You?**\r\n1. Find an inactive Customer and reactivate any entity under them (Users, Districts, Schools, and/or Classrooms).\r\n2. Run this script from the Rails console.\r\n3. Check to see that the reactivated entity is now deactivated again.\r\n4. SUCCESS!!!\r\n\r\n**Why Does This Work?**\r\nUnder the Customer model there is a `after_update` callback that checks to see if the Customer's `status` attribute is set to _inactive_, and if so it will go through the fix I've added in the Pull Request mentioned above. I've confirmed that the `after_update` callback gets called, even if no attributes were updated.",
     "closed_at" => nil,
